#. TRANSLATORS: Message title for a piece of information
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/init.lua:33
msgid "Note"
msgstr "Pastaba"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/init.lua:34
msgid ""
"You appear not to have completed the previous mission. You may still play "
"this scenario, but you will be at a disadvantage. I recommend that you "
"complete the previous scenario first and then restart this mission."
msgstr ""
"Atrodo, kad neatlikote ankstesnės misijos. Vis tiek galite žaisti šį "
"scenarijų, bet būsite nepalankioje padėtyje. Rekomenduoju pirmiausia "
"užbaigti ankstesnį scenarijų ir tada iš naujo pradėti šią misiją."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:25
msgid "Build a basic economy"
msgstr "Sukurkite pagrindinę ekonomiką"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:27
msgid "Supply All Basic Materials"
msgstr "Tiekti visas pagrindines medžiagas"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:28
msgid ""
"Build a quarry, a reed farm, a clay pit, a well, a charcoal kiln, a brick "
"kiln, and houses for a woodcutter and a forester."
msgstr ""
"Pastatykite karjerą, nendrių fermą, molio duobę, šulinį, medžio anglies "
"krosnį, plytų krosnį ir namus medžio pjaustytojui ir miškininkui."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:33
msgid "Expand to the south"
msgstr "Plėsti į pietus"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:35
msgid "Expand Your Territory to Explore the South"
msgstr "Išplėskite savo teritoriją ir tyrinėkite pietus"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:36
msgid ""
"The north looks not very useful to us, but who knows what we might find in "
"the south?"
msgstr ""
"Šiaurė mums atrodo nelabai naudinga, bet kas žino, ką galime rasti pietuose?"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:41
msgid "Train and recycle"
msgstr "Treniruokis ir perdirbk"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:43
msgid "Recycle Weapons to Regain Metal"
msgstr "Perdirbkite ginklus, kad atgautumėte metalą"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:44
msgid ""
"When soldiers train, their old weapons are discarded. They can be turned "
"into metal in a recycling center. Use the weapons in the store to train "
"soldiers and recycle some scrap metal."
msgstr ""
"Kai kariai treniruojasi, jų seni ginklai išmetami. Perdirbimo centre juos "
"galima paversti metalu. Parduotuvėje esančius ginklus mokykite karius ir "
"perdirbkite metalo laužą."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:45
msgid ""
"The blacksmithy only produces a pick in its second production cycle. If it "
"is supplied with only one iron ingot at a time, it might never reach this "
"cycle. You need to stop the blacksmithy until at least two iron are stored "
"in its input queue."
msgstr ""
"Kalvystė gamina tik antrąjį gamybos ciklą. Jei vienu metu tiekiamas tik "
"vienas geležies luitas, jis gali niekada nepasiekti šio ciklo. Turite "
"sustabdyti kalvį, kol bent dvi geležies bus saugomos jos įvesties eilėje."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:50
msgid "Build an aqua farm"
msgstr "Sukurkite vandens ūkį"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:52
msgid "Build an Aqua Farm to Start Producing Fish"
msgstr "Sukurkite vandens ūkį, kad pradėtumėte gaminti žuvį"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:53
msgid ""
"Build an aqua farm to produce fish. The aqua farm needs the holes left by a "
"clay pit nearby to use as ponds to grow fish in. Only a fisher working at an"
" aqua farm can fish from these ponds."
msgstr ""
"Sukurkite vandens ūkį žuvims gaminti. Vandens ūkiui reikia skylių, kurias "
"paliko šalia esančios molio duobės, kad būtų galima naudoti kaip tvenkinius "
"žuvims auginti. Iš šių tvenkinių žvejoti gali tik žvejys, dirbantis vandens "
"ūkyje."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:58
msgid "Decide whether you want to cooperate with the Empire"
msgstr "Nuspręskite, ar norite bendradarbiauti su imperija"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:60
msgid "Gather Wares as a Gift or Destroy the Empire’s Warehouse"
msgstr "Surinkite gaminius kaip dovaną arba sunaikinkite imperijos sandėlį"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:61
msgid ""
"Decide whether you want to work with Murilius against the Barbarians. If so,"
" fill his warehouse with these wares:"
msgstr ""
"Nuspręskite, ar norite dirbti su Muriliumi prieš barbarus. Jei taip, "
"užpildykite jo sandėlį šiais gaminiais:"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:62
msgid "30 × Log"
msgstr "30 × rastai"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:63
msgid "40 × Granite"
msgstr "40 × granitas"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:64
msgid "30 × Fish"
msgstr "30 × žuvis"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:65
msgid "30 × Beer"
msgstr "30 × alus"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:66
msgid "150 × Water"
msgstr "150 × vanduo"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:67
msgid "40 × Ration"
msgstr "40 × racionas"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:68
msgid "10 × Meal"
msgstr "10 × patiekalas"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:69
msgid "30 × Coal"
msgstr "30 × anglis"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:70
msgid "40 × Iron Ore"
msgstr "40 × geležies rūda"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:71
msgid "20 × Iron"
msgstr "20 × geležis"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:72
msgid "20 × Gold Ore"
msgstr "20 × aukso rūda"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:73
msgid "10 × Gold"
msgstr "10 × auksas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Continues from "Decide whether you want to work with Murilius
#. against the Barbarians. If so, fill his warehouse with these wares: [list
#. of wares]"
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:75
msgid ""
"Otherwise, just destroy the warehouse and risk having Murilius as an enemy. "
"He forbade you to expand your territory until the wares have been handed "
"over."
msgstr ""
"Priešingu atveju tiesiog sunaikinkite sandėlį ir rizikuokite, kad Murilius "
"bus priešas. Jis uždraudė jums plėsti savo teritoriją, kol prekės nebus "
"perduotos."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:80
msgid "Spy on Murilius"
msgstr "Šnipinėja Murilius"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:82
msgid "Send a Scout to Spy on the Empire"
msgstr "Nusiųskite žvalgą šnipinėti imperiją"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:83
msgid ""
"Build a scout’s house near the border to discover the Empire’s secrets."
msgstr ""
"Pastatykite skautų namą netoli sienos, kad sužinotumėte imperijos paslaptis."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:88
msgid "Decipher the poem"
msgstr "Iššifruokite eilėraštį"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:90
msgid "Understand the Poem the Scout has Found in the Empire"
msgstr "Supraskite eilėraštį, kurį skautas rado imperijoje"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Expansion hint. A poem, verse 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:91
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:336
msgid "How many sites where soldiers stay,"
msgstr "kiek vietų, kur apsistoja kariai,"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Expansion hint. A poem, verse 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:92
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:339
msgid "How many sites where thou hold’st sway,"
msgstr "Kiek vietų, kuriose tu laikai siūbavimą,"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Expansion hint. A poem, verse 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:93
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:342
msgid "Though not their whereabouts sees he"
msgstr "nors ir ne jų buvimo vieta"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Expansion hint. A poem, verse 4
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:94
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:345
msgid "Who’s ordering around here thee!"
msgstr "Kas čia užsisako, tu!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:99
msgid "Defeat the Barbarians!"
msgstr "Nugalėk barbarus!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:101
msgid "Defeat the Barbarians"
msgstr "Nugalėk barbarus"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:102
msgid "Defeat the hostile tribe living northwest of the Empire’s outpost!"
msgstr ""
"Nugalėk priešišką gentį, gyvenančią į šiaurės vakarus nuo imperijos "
"forposto!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:107
msgid "Defeat Murilius!"
msgstr "Nugalėk Murilius!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:109
msgid "Defeat the Arrogant Outpost of the Empire"
msgstr "Nugalėk arogantišką imperijos forpostą"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:110
msgid ""
"The only way to put an end to the Empire’s desire to steal our liberty is to"
" destroy this outpost once and for all. Conquer its entire land."
msgstr ""
"Vienintelis būdas padaryti galą imperijos norui pavogti mūsų laisvę yra "
"kartą ir visiems laikams sunaikinti šį forpostą. užkariauti visą jos žemę."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:111
msgid "Conquer every single field that still belongs to Murilius."
msgstr "Užkariaukite kiekvieną lauką, kuris vis dar priklauso Muriliui."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:116
msgid "Defeat Murilius and the Barbarians!"
msgstr "Nugalėk Murilių ir barbarus!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:118
msgid "Defeat the Barbarians and the Empire Colony"
msgstr "Nugalėk barbarus ir imperijos koloniją"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:119
msgid ""
"The Barbarians and the Empire are too dangerous to allow them to live near "
"us. We must defeat them both."
msgstr ""
"Barbarai ir imperija yra pernelyg pavojingi, kad leistų jiems gyventi šalia "
"mūsų. Turime juos abu nugalėti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:128
msgid ""
"I began to believe the journey would never end. I have no idea how long we "
"were at sea, tossed about by envious storms… it must have been months."
msgstr ""
"Pradėjau tikėti, kad kelionė niekada nesibaigs. Neįsivaizduoju, kiek laiko "
"buvome jūroje, mėtosi pavydžių audrų... Turbūt praėjo mėnesiai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:130
msgid ""
"The storms maintained a firm grip on the ship throughout our voyage. There "
"was hardly a day on which we did not wonder whether it would be our last. We"
" were compelled to drop the precious metals we had taken with us overboard "
"to steady the ship, feeling as though it were a squalid sacrifice to the "
"gods to give us hope to live a few hours longer."
msgstr ""
"Audros tvirtai laikė laivą visos mūsų kelionės metu. Vargu ar buvo tokia "
"diena, kai nesusimąstytume, ar tai bus paskutinė. Buvome priversti numesti "
"tauriuosius metalus, kuriuos pasiėmėme su savimi už borto, kad sutvirtintume"
" laivą, jausdami, lyg tai būtų niūri auka dievams, suteikianti mums vilties "
"gyventi dar kelias valandas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:132
msgid ""
"The few tools we managed to salvage from Langeness did not cope well. The "
"miners’ picks proved especially vulnerable, and we had to throw them in the "
"ocean when it became evident that they had been corroded by the sea salt so "
"much that we could never again mine anything with them."
msgstr ""
"Keletas įrankių, kuriuos mums pavyko išgelbėti iš langeness, nebuvo gerai "
"susitvarkę. Kalnakasių kirtikliai pasirodė ypač pažeidžiami, ir mes turėjome"
" juos išmesti į vandenyną, kai paaiškėjo, kad juos taip surūdijo jūros "
"druska, kad daugiau niekada nieko negalėsime su jais išgauti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:134
msgid ""
"But we survived. Finally, we reached the mouth of a calmer fjord. We sailed "
"upriver, and arrived here."
msgstr ""
"Bet mes išgyvenome. Galiausiai pasiekėme ramesnio fiordo žiotis. Išplaukėme "
"aukštyn ir čia atvykome."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:140
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:145
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:154
msgid "Welcome Back!"
msgstr "Sveiki sugrįžę!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:141
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:146
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:155
msgid "A new home"
msgstr "Nauji namai"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:148
msgid ""
"There was a small group of foreigners living here. They welcomed us by "
"brandishing their axes at us, and shouted in an incoherent language."
msgstr ""
"Čia gyveno nedidelė grupė užsieniečių. Jie mus pasitiko mojuodami į mus savo"
" kirviais ir šaukė nenuoseklia kalba."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:151
msgid ""
"Our ship was in no state to continue sailing, so we killed the locals and "
"took their land. I just hope there aren’t more of them, so we can live in "
"peace."
msgstr ""
"Mūsų laivas nebuvo valstybėje, kad galėtume toliau plaukti, todėl nužudėme "
"vietinius gyventojus ir paėmėme jų žemę. Tikiuosi, kad jų nebus daugiau, kad"
" galėtume gyventi taikiai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:157
msgid ""
"This place looks bleak and barren, my companions say, but I think it looks… "
"beautiful."
msgstr ""
"Ši vieta atrodo niūri ir nevaisinga, sako mano palydovai, bet manau, kad ji "
"atrodo... gražiai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:160
msgid ""
"My scouts no longer report any signs of living creatures nearby. We will "
"start building our new home here."
msgstr ""
"Mano skautai nebepraneša apie gyvų būtybių požymius netoliese. Čia pradėsime"
" statyti savo naujus namus."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Introduction 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:163
msgid ""
"We must start by building all the basic buildings. I see no mountains nearby"
" where we might mine coal. We’d better build a charcoal kiln to burn logs "
"into charcoal. We improve the kilns with clay so they don’t consume so much "
"wood. Our neighbors used to envy us for this clever technique, which they "
"couldn’t copy."
msgstr ""
"Turime pradėti nuo visų pagrindinių pastatų statybos. Netoliese nematau "
"kalnų, kur galėtume išgauti anglį. Geriau pastatyti anglies krosnį, kad "
"sudegintume rąstus į anglį. Krosnis tobuliname moliu, kad jos nesunaudotų "
"tiek daug medienos. Mūsų kaimynai mums pavydėjo šiai protingai technikai, "
"kurios negalėjo kopijuoti."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:168
msgid "Go South"
msgstr "Eik į pietus"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:169
msgid "Expand and conquer"
msgstr "Plėsti ir užkariauti"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Expand South
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:171
msgid ""
"We have built a home in this wonderful landscape. But as our tribe grows, we"
" need more space. We should start expanding our territory."
msgstr ""
"Šiame nuostabiame kraštovaizdyje pasistatėme namus. Tačiau augant mūsų "
"genčiai, mums reikia daugiau erdvės. Turėtume pradėti plėsti savo "
"teritoriją."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Expand South
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:174
msgid ""
"The scouts reported that the lands to the north are rugged hills, beautiful "
"to behold but not suited for buildings. Let’s find out what we can discover "
"in the south."
msgstr ""
"Skautai pranešė, kad šiaurėje esančios žemės yra tvirtos kalvos, gražios, "
"bet netinka pastatams. Išsiaiškinkime, ką galime atrasti pietuose."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:179
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:188
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:197
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:207
msgid "Metal Shortage"
msgstr "Metalo trūkumas"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:180
msgid "We are out of metals"
msgstr "Mums baigėsi metalai"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Train and recycle 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:182
msgid ""
"Chieftain Reebaud! We have a serious problem. We have discovered a mountain "
"where we might be able to start mining coal and iron, but we have no miners,"
" nor any picks to equip them with."
msgstr ""
"Vyriausiasis Reebaud! Turime rimtą problemą. Atradome kalną, kuriame "
"galėtume pradėti kasti anglį ir geležį, bet neturime nei kalnakasių, nei "
"pasirinkimų, kuriais galėtume juos aprūpinti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Train and recycle 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:185
msgid ""
"And we don’t have any iron left. We must find a way to get some metal for "
"forging new picks. Unfortunately, I have no idea how to do this."
msgstr ""
"Ir mums nebelieka geležies. Turime rasti būdą, kaip gauti metalo naujiems "
"pasirinkimams kalti. Deja, aš neįsivaizduoju, kaip tai padaryti."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:189
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:208
msgid "Getting new metal"
msgstr "Naujo metalo gavimas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Train and recycle 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:191
msgid ""
"This is terrible news! Without iron or the means to produce any, we are "
"stuck like this forever! You must come up with a solution."
msgstr ""
"Tai baisi žinia! Be geležies ar priemonių gaminti, mes taip įstrigome "
"amžiams! Turite sugalvoti sprendimą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Train and recycle 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:194
msgid ""
"I have seen some advanced weapons in our warehouses. Perhaps it would be "
"possible to smelt them back into metal? But that seems like a waste of the "
"precious swords…"
msgstr ""
"Mačiau keletą pažangių ginklų mūsų sandėliuose. Galbūt būtų galima juos "
"išlydyti atgal į metalą? Bet tai atrodo kaip brangių kardų švaistymas..."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:198
msgid "New metal"
msgstr "Naujas metalas"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Train and recycle 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:200
msgid ""
"Now I have an idea: When our soldiers are trained, they are equipped with "
"new swords and the old weapons are discarded. These are unfit to use in "
"battle, so it would not be a waste to smelt down those."
msgstr ""
"Dabar turiu idėją: kai mūsų kariai yra apmokyti, jie aprūpinti naujais "
"kardais, o senieji ginklai išmetami. Jie netinkami naudoti mūšyje, todėl "
"juos lydyti nebūtų veltui."

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Train and recycle 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:203
msgid ""
"That is what we must do. We will use our weapons to train soldiers, then "
"smelt the scrap metal into iron and gold. And then our blacksmiths can "
"produce picks to equip miners with. I will see to it at once!"
msgstr ""
"Tai mes turime padaryti. Mes naudosime savo ginklus kariams mokyti, tada "
"metalo laužą išlydysime į geležį ir auksą. Ir tada mūsų kalviai gali gaminti"
" kirtiklius, kad aprūpintų kalnakasius. Iš karto pasirūpinsiu!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Train and recycle 4
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:210
msgid ""
"Not so hasty! To build a training camp, we will first need gold, and we "
"don’t have any. We must first dismantle our port, which will give us just "
"enough gold for a training camp. I don’t like this, but it is the only way. "
"Of course, we will need to move all our wares to a warehouse before we can "
"dismantle the port."
msgstr ""
"Ne taip skubotai! Norėdami sukurti treniruočių stovyklą, pirmiausia mums "
"reikės aukso, o mes jo neturime. Pirmiausia turime išardyti savo uostą, "
"kuris suteiks mums tik tiek aukso treniruočių stovyklai. Man tai nepatinka, "
"bet tai vienintelis būdas. Žinoma, prieš išmontuodami uostą turėsime "
"perkelti visus savo gaminius į sandėlį."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:214
msgid "Metal Production"
msgstr "Metalo gamyba"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:215
msgid "The mines are working"
msgstr "Kasyklos veikia"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Aqua Farms 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:217
msgid ""
"Our mines have started working. Now, we only need to build a furnace and the"
" metal production will be running smoothly."
msgstr ""
"Mūsų kasyklos pradėjo veikti. Dabar mums tereikia pastatyti krosnį ir metalo"
" gamyba vyks sklandžiai."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Aqua Farms 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:220
msgid ""
"Do we have a reindeer farm already? If not, we should build one now. We need"
" more reindeer for the crowded roads, and we could already start sewing fur "
"garments to equip new soldiers. Who knows whether we will have to fight "
"eventually?"
msgstr ""
"Ar jau turime šiaurės elnių fermą? Jei ne, turėtume sukurti vieną dabar. "
"Mums reikia daugiau šiaurės elnių perpildytuose keliuose ir jau galėtume "
"pradėti siūti kailinius drabužius, kad aprūpintume naujus karius. Kas žino, "
"ar galiausiai turėsime kovoti?"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:223
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:233
msgid "Fishing"
msgstr "Žvejyba"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:224
msgid "We need fish"
msgstr "Mums reikia žuvies"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Aqua Farms 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:226
msgid ""
"Chieftain Reebaud, I have more bad news. There are almost no fish in the "
"waters nearby. While we can prepare rations using only fruit or bread, "
"soldier training requires lots of smoked meat or fish. The scraps of meat a "
"reindeer farm drops out as a by-product when making fur aren’t enough."
msgstr ""
"Viršininkas Reebaud, turiu daugiau blogų naujienų. Netoliese esančiuose "
"vandenyse žuvų beveik nėra. Nors racioną galime paruošti naudodami tik "
"vaisius ar duoną, kareivių mokymui reikia daug rūkytos mėsos ar žuvies. "
"Mėsos likučiai šiaurės elnių fermoje iškrenta kaip šalutinis produktas, kai "
"gaminant kailį neužtenka."

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Aqua Farms 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:229
msgid ""
"Fortunately, one of our fishermen thought of a solution. Our clay pits leave"
" large holes in the ground; a fisher could fill them with water and grow "
"fish in these ponds. He will only need lots of water for the ponds, and "
"fruit to feed the fish."
msgstr ""
"Laimei, vienas iš mūsų žvejų sugalvojo sprendimą. Mūsų molio duobės palieka "
"dideles skyles žemėje; Žvejas galėtų pripilti juos vandens ir auginti žuvis "
"šiuose tvenkiniuose. Jam reikės tik daug vandens tvenkiniams ir vaisių "
"žuvims maitinti."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:234
msgid "We have fish again"
msgstr "Vėl turime žuvies"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Aqua Farms 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:236
msgid ""
"Well done. We have built an aqua farm, and our mining economy is stable for "
"now. However, the miners tell me that the resources are already low, and the"
" mines may run completely empty soon."
msgstr ""
"Gerai padaryta. Mes pastatėme vandens ūkį, o mūsų kasybos ekonomika kol kas "
"stabili. Tačiau kalnakasiai man sako, kad išteklių jau mažai, o kasyklos "
"netrukus gali veikti visiškai tuščios."

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Aqua Farms 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:239
msgid ""
"The mines will still be able to produce then, but it will take about twenty "
"times longer – ten times if it is a deep mine – to produce ores or coal. You"
" probably want to prepare for the increasing demands of time and food."
msgstr ""
"Tada kasyklos vis tiek galės gaminti, bet užtruks maždaug dvidešimt kartų "
"ilgiau – dešimt kartų, jei tai gilioji kasykla – rūdos ar anglies gamyba. "
"Tikriausiai norite pasiruošti didėjantiems laiko ir maisto poreikiams."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:242
msgid "Recruiting"
msgstr "Komplektavimas"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:243
msgid "Our economy is complete"
msgstr "Mūsų ekonomika baigta"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Aqua Farms 4
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:245
msgid ""
"You are right – we should build more berry farms, fruit collector’s houses "
"and taverns as well as a drinking hall, and advanced bakeries and breweries."
msgstr ""
"Jūs teisus – turėtume pastatyti daugiau uogų fermų, vaisių kolekcinių namų "
"ir tavernų, taip pat gėrimų salę, pažangias kepyklas ir alaus daryklas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Aqua Farms 4
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:248
msgid ""
"However, we can already start focusing on recruiting and training soldiers. "
"We can now afford to use metal for weapons, helmets and garments. I propose "
"building armor smithies, a barracks, a training arena and a tailor’s shop "
"now."
msgstr ""
"Tačiau jau galime pradėti sutelkti dėmesį į karių įdarbinimą ir mokymą. "
"Dabar galime sau leisti naudoti metalą ginklams, šalmams ir drabužiams. "
"Dabar siūlau statyti šarvus, kareivines, mokymo areną ir siuvėjų parduotuvę."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:252
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:259
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:265
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:274
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:280
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:289
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:298
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:304
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:314
msgid "We Are Not Alone"
msgstr "Mes nesame vieni"

#. TRANSLATORS: "Greetings, strangers!". DO NOT TRANSLATE. Reebaud doesn’t
#. understand Latin. You can transliterate into non-Latin scripts though
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:254
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:266
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:281
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:290
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:305
msgid "Salvete peregrini!"
msgstr "Salvete Peregrini!"

#. TRANSLATORS: "Be greeted, strangers! I am Proconsule Murilius of the
#. province 'The Northern Lands'. Name yourselves!". DO NOT TRANSLATE. Reebaud
#. doesn’t understand Latin. You can transliterate into non-Latin scripts
#. though
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:256
msgid ""
"Salvete peregrini! Murilius Proconsul Terrae Septentrionalis provinciae ego "
"sum. Vos nominate!"
msgstr ""
"Salvete Peregrini! Murilius proconsul terrae septentrionalis provinciae ego "
"suma. Vos nominuoti!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:260
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:275
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:299
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:315
msgid "Strangers"
msgstr "Svetimšaliai"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Supply Murilius 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:262
msgid "…does anyone understand what he is saying?"
msgstr "...Ar kas nors supranta, ką jis sako?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 3. This is a foreign language to
#. Murilius, so he sounds very formal.
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:268
msgid "Do they not even speak the noble language of the Empire?"
msgstr "Ar jie net nekalba kilnia imperijos kalba?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 3
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:271
msgid ""
"Strangers! I, Murilius, Proconsul of the Northern Lands, a province of the "
"Empire, demand to know who you are and what business you have in these "
"lands!"
msgstr ""
"Nepažįstami žmonės! Aš, Murilius, Šiaurės žemių prokonsulas, imperijos "
"provincija, reikalauju sužinoti, kas tu esi ir kokį verslą šiose žemėse "
"turi!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Supply Murilius 4. "Peace" is the traditional
#. Frisian greeting, nothing more.
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:277
msgid ""
"Peace, representative of the Empire! I am Reebaud, the chieftain of this "
"tribe. All we want is to settle down here, build our home and live our lives"
" in peace. We do not seek trouble, but we aren’t afraid to fight, either."
msgstr ""
"Taika, imperijos atstove! Aš esu Reebaud, šios genties vadas. Viskas, ko mes"
" norime, yra čia įsikurti, pasistatyti savo namus ir gyventi taikiai. Mes "
"nesiekiame bėdų, bet ir nebijome kovoti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 5. "Reebaude" is the Latin vocative
#. case (form of address) of Reebaud.
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:283
msgid ""
"In this case, Reebaude, I must inform you of the presence of an "
"inhospitable, hostile tribe of Barbarians in the vicinity of this very "
"outpost of the Empire."
msgstr ""
"Šiuo atveju, Reebaude, turiu jus informuoti apie nesvetingą, priešišką "
"barbarų gentį, esančią netoli šio imperijos forposto."

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 5
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:286
msgid ""
"If you seek to live peacefully here, you are not faced with a choice whether"
" to allow them to live here – you are required to assist the Empire in "
"driving them out."
msgstr ""
"Jei siekiate čia gyventi taikiai, jūs neturite pasirinkimo, ar leisti jiems "
"čia gyventi – jūs turite padėti imperijai juos išvaryti."

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 6
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:292
msgid ""
"Also, as a sign of your good intentions, we demand a gift of friendship to "
"the Empire. As you should have noticed, I have presented you with a new "
"warehouse. Fill it with the required gifts to hand them over. I permit you "
"to give us these wares:"
msgstr ""
"Be to, kaip jūsų gerų ketinimų ženklą, reikalaujame draugystės dovanos "
"imperijai. Kaip ir turėjote pastebėti, aš jums pateikiau naują sandėlį. "
"Užpildykite jį reikalingomis dovanomis, kad jas įteiktumėte. Leidžiu jums "
"duoti mums šiuos gaminius:"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 6. A list of wares.
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:295
msgid ""
"30 logs, 40 slabs of granite, 30 fish, 30 mugs of beer, 150 buckets of "
"water, 40 rations, 10 meals, 30 lumps of coal, 40 lumps of iron ore, 20 iron"
" ingots, 20 lumps of gold ore, and 10 gold bars."
msgstr ""
"30 rąstų, 40 granito plokščių, 30 žuvų, 30 bokalų alaus, 150 kibirų vandens,"
" 40 davinių, 10 patiekalų, 30 gabalėlių anglies, 40 gabalėlių geležies Rūda,"
" 20 geležies luitų, 20 gabalėlių aukso rūdos ir 10 aukso luitų."

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Supply Murilius 7
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:301
msgid ""
"Chieftain Reebaud – the demands of this arrogant Empire Proconsul are just "
"outrageous. He treats us like we are his servants. And we certainly cannot "
"afford to spare that many wares to aid him. I propose that we destroy that "
"ugly warehouse and let him fight his own battles."
msgstr ""
"Chieftain Reebaud – šios arogantiškos imperijos Proconsul reikalavimai yra "
"tiesiog siaubingi. Jis elgiasi su mumis kaip su Jo tarnais. Ir tikrai "
"negalime sau leisti nepagailėti tiek daug prekių, kad jam padėtų. Siūlau "
"sugriauti tą bjaurų sandėlį ir leisti jam kovoti savo kovas."

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 8
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:307
msgid ""
"If you fail to deliver these wares, the Empire shall treat you like enemies."
" And so as to prevent you wasting your precious metal, I forbid you to "
"expand your territory from this moment on until you have given us your gift."
" Fail to obey, and the Empire shall treat you like enemies."
msgstr ""
"Jei jums nepavyks pristatyti šių gaminių, imperija elgsis su jumis kaip su "
"priešais. Ir kad neleisčiau švaistyti savo tauriojo metalo, uždrausiu plėsti"
" savo teritoriją nuo šios akimirkos, kol nepadovanosite mums savo dovanos. "
"nepaklus, ir imperija elgsis su tavimi kaip su priešais."

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supply Murilius 8
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:310
msgid ""
"You will have to fight those Barbarians if you intend to live in the area; "
"surely you can see that fighting them together with the Empire is easier "
"than alone? And you really do not want the Empire as your enemy. Barbarians "
"though you are, I do believe you will realize the truth of my words after "
"some consideration."
msgstr ""
"Jei ketinate gyventi rajone, turėsite kovoti su barbarais; Ar tikrai matote,"
" kad kovoti su jais kartu su imperija yra lengviau nei vienam? Ir jūs tikrai"
" nenorite, kad imperija būtų jūsų priešas. Nors ir barbarai, aš tikiu, kad "
"po tam tikro svarstymo suprasite mano žodžių tiesą."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Supply Murilius 9
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:317
msgid ""
"This is the greatest outrage of all. How dare he order us to stop expanding "
"our territory when all we want is to build a new home, and threaten us with "
"war if we refuse to be his slaves?"
msgstr ""
"Tai didžiausias pasipiktinimas iš visų. Kaip Jis drįsta mums įsakyti nustoti"
" plėsti savo teritoriją, kai norime tik pastatyti naujus namus ir grasinti "
"mums karu, jei atsisakysime būti Jo vergais?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Supply Murilius 9
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:320
msgid ""
"I’d like to say we should attack him right now, but I fear we aren’t strong "
"enough yet to hold our own against him in battle. We should hurry our "
"soldier training while pretending to be gathering his so-called gift. That "
"would buy us some time."
msgstr ""
"Norėčiau pasakyti, kad turėtume jį pulti dabar, bet bijau, kad dar nesame "
"pakankamai stiprūs, kad galėtume atsilaikyti prieš jį mūšyje. Turėtume "
"paskubinti savo kareivio mokymus, apsimesdami, kad renkame jo vadinamąją "
"dovaną. Tai mums atpirktų šiek tiek laiko."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – Supply Murilius 9
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:323
msgid ""
"As for expansion – I wonder how strictly he can possibly control us. Perhaps"
" we should send a scout to spy on him…"
msgstr ""
"Kalbant apie plėtrą – įdomu, kaip griežtai jis gali mus kontroliuoti. Galbūt"
" turėtume nusiųsti žvalgą, kad jis šnipinėtų jį..."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:330
msgid "The Scout Discovered Something"
msgstr "Skautas kažką atrado"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:331
msgid "Our scout returned"
msgstr "Mūsų skautas grįžo"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Expansion hint
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:333
msgid ""
"Chieftain Reebaud! Our scout just returned. He has found a poem in the "
"strange tongue this Proconsul speaks. With some difficulty, I have "
"translated it into our language. If I did not mistranslate, it runs as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""
"Vyriausiasis Reebaud! Mūsų skautas ką tik grįžo. Jis rado eilėraštį keista "
"kalba, kurią kalba šis prokonsulas. Su tam tikrais sunkumais išverčiau jį į "
"mūsų kalbą. Jei nesuklydau neteisingai, jis veikia taip:"

#. TRANSLATORS: Hauke – Expansion hint
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:348
msgid ""
"I don’t know what it means, but I’m sure it’s important. Perhaps you can "
"make some sense of it."
msgstr ""
"Nežinau, ką tai reiškia, bet esu tikras, kad tai svarbu. Galbūt galite tai "
"suprasti."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:353
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:363
msgid "The Empire is Angry"
msgstr "Imperija pikta"

#. TRANSLATORS: "You are enemies of the Empire!". DO NOT TRANSLATE. Reebaud
#. doesn’t understand Latin. You can transliterate into non-Latin scripts
#. though
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:355
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:364
msgid "Hostes Imperii estis!"
msgstr "Šeimininkai imperii estis!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – enemy of the Empire: player destroyed the warehouse
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:357
msgid ""
"Barbarians! You have refused my offer of friendship most ungraciously by "
"destroying the beautiful building we presented you with!"
msgstr ""
"Barbarai! Jūs negailestingiausiai atsisakėte mano pasiūlymo draugauti, "
"sunaikindami gražų pastatą, kurį jums padovanojome!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – enemy of the Empire
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:360
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:369
msgid "You are enemies of the Empire, and I shall treat you as such!"
msgstr "Jūs esate imperijos priešai, ir aš elgsiuosi su jumis kaip su tokiu!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – enemy of the Empire: player built forbidden
#. military buildings
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:366
msgid ""
"Barbarians! You have refused my offer of friendship most ungraciously by "
"basely wasting your precious resources on expansion!"
msgstr ""
"Barbarai! Jūs negailestingiausiai atsisakėte mano pasiūlymo draugauti, nes "
"iššvaistydami savo brangius išteklius plėtrai!"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:372
msgid "Two Enemies"
msgstr "Du priešai"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:373
msgid "Defeat the enemies!"
msgstr "Nugalėk priešus!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – defeat both enemies
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:375
msgid ""
"Murilius has made it quite clear that he won’t leave us alone. I fear we "
"must defeat him and destroy his colony if we ever want to have peace here."
msgstr ""
"Murilius aiškiai pasakė, kad nepaliks mūsų ramybėje. Bijau, kad turime jį "
"nugalėti ir sunaikinti jo koloniją, jei kada nors norime čia turėti taiką."

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – defeat both enemies
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:378
msgid ""
"The Barbarian tribe he mentioned is also a threat. I don’t want to share "
"this land with anyone, as sharing only leads to conflicts and battles, as we"
" saw in our old home. We must defeat the Barbarians as well."
msgstr ""
"Jo minėta barbarų gentis taip pat kelia grėsmę. Nenoriu su niekuo dalytis "
"šia žeme, nes dalijimasis tik veda į konfliktus ir mūšius, kaip matėme savo "
"senuose namuose. Turime nugalėti ir barbarus."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:382
msgid "The Empire is Grateful"
msgstr "Imperija yra dėkinga"

#. TRANSLATORS: "Greetings, friends of the Empire!". DO NOT TRANSLATE. Reebaud
#. doesn’t understand Latin. You can transliterate into non-Latin scripts
#. though
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:384
msgid "Salvete amici Imperii!"
msgstr "Salvete amici imperii!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supplied Murilius
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:386
msgid ""
"Strangers! I see you have kept your word. The Empire rewards its friends, "
"therefore I shall reward you with the friendship of the Empire!"
msgstr ""
"Nepažįstami žmonės! Matau, kad ištesėjote savo žodį. Imperija apdovanoja "
"savo draugus, todėl aš apdovanosiu jus imperijos draugyste!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – Supplied Murilius. Murilius’s plan is to use the
#. player as cannon fodder, while he himself only attacks when he has no
#. choice
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:389
msgid ""
"Now I permit you to assist us in conquering the Barbarians, who live in a "
"sheltered valley northwest to us. I charge you, expand along the northern "
"end of the mountains enclosing this outpost; you will find the Barbarians "
"there – attack them! We will fend off attacks launched by the enemy."
msgstr ""
"Dabar leidžiu jums padėti mums užkariauti barbarus, kurie gyvena apsaugotame"
" slėnyje į šiaurės vakarus nuo mūsų. Aš įkraunu jus, išsiplėskite palei "
"šiaurinį kalnų galą, gaubiantį šį forpostą; Ten rasite barbarus – pulkite "
"juos! Mes atremsime priešo pradėtas atakas."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:393
msgid "The Reward For Your Service"
msgstr "Atlygis už jūsų paslaugą"

#. TRANSLATORS: "Friends of the Empire". DO NOT TRANSLATE. Reebaud doesn’t
#. understand Latin. You can transliterate into non-Latin scripts though
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:395
msgid "Amici Imperii"
msgstr "amici imperii"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – defeat Murilius 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:397
msgid ""
"You have done well, strangers! As I did tell you earlier, you will be "
"rewarded with the friendship of the Empire!"
msgstr ""
"Jūs padarėte gerai, nepažįstami žmonės! Kaip jau sakiau anksčiau, būsite "
"apdovanoti imperijos draugyste!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Murilius – defeat Murilius 1
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:400
msgid ""
"I propose you start by sending legates to the Capital, so as to discover the"
" most recent political activities. Once there, you can receive instructions "
"for your tribe from the Senate. Also, you will need to find out what tribute"
" the Capital will demand from you, and of course, who shall be king of your "
"tribe."
msgstr ""
"Siūlau pradėti nuo legatų siuntimo į sostinę, kad atrastumėte naujausią "
"politinę veiklą. Ten patekę galite gauti nurodymus savo genčiai iš Senato. "
"Be to, turėsite išsiaiškinti, kokios duoklės iš jūsų pareikalaus sostinė ir,"
" žinoma, kas bus jūsų genties karalius."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:403
msgid "Another Enemy"
msgstr "Kitas priešas"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:404
msgid "Defeat the Empire!"
msgstr "Nugalėk imperiją!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – defeat Murilius 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:406
msgid ""
"Did I understand him correctly? After all we have done for him, after so "
"many of my soldiers have laid down their lives for his sake, he wants us to "
"be servants of this Empire, and take away my leadership? And does the "
"hypocrite dare call this a reward?"
msgstr ""
"Ar teisingai jį supratau? Po visko, ką padarėme dėl jo, po to, kai tiek daug"
" mano karių atidavė savo gyvybes dėl jo, jis nori, kad būtume šios imperijos"
" tarnai ir atimtume mano vadovavimą? Ir ar veidmainis išdrįsta tai vadinti "
"atlygiu?"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – defeat Murilius 2
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:409
msgid ""
"We will punish this self-proclaimed Proconsul for his treachery! I shall "
"burn down his entire colony, and kill every single person in his realm. He "
"will be very sorry indeed for insulting our tribe thus."
msgstr ""
"Mes nubausime šį apsišaukėlį prokonsulą už jo išdavystę! Aš sudeginsiu visą "
"jo koloniją ir nužudysiu kiekvieną žmogų jo karalystėje. Jis tikrai labai "
"gailisi, kad taip įžeidė mūsų gentį."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:413
msgid "Victory"
msgstr "Pergalė"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:414
msgid "Victory!"
msgstr "Pergalė!"

#. TRANSLATORS: Reebaud – victory
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:416
msgid ""
"We have defeated all our enemies! Now no other tribe will ever dare settle "
"here again. We are safe, and we can finally live our lives in peace."
msgstr ""
"Mes nugalėjome visus savo priešus! Dabar jokia kita gentis niekada nebedrįs "
"čia apsigyventi. Esame saugūs ir pagaliau galime gyventi taikiai."

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:417
msgid "Congratulations"
msgstr "Sveikiname"

#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:418
msgid ""
"You have completed this mission. You may continue playing if you wish, "
"otherwise move on to the next mission."
msgstr ""
"Jūs įvykdėte šią misiją. Jei norite, galite toliau žaisti, kitaip pereikite "
"prie kitos misijos."

#. TRANSLATORS: Purpose helptext for an Empire warehouse: Warehouse
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/tribes/init.lua:13
msgctxt "empire_building"
msgid ""
"Your workers and soldiers will find shelter here. Also stores your wares and"
" tools."
msgstr ""
"Jūsų darbuotojai ir kariai čia ras prieglobstį. Taip pat saugo jūsų prekes "
"ir įrankius."

#. TRANSLATORS: This is a building name used in lists of buildings
#: ../../../../data/campaigns/fri02.wmf/scripting/tribes/warehouse/init.lua:8
msgctxt "frisians_building"
msgid "Empire Warehouse"
msgstr "Empire Warehouse"
